article.headline: North Carolina A&T beats Bethune-Cookman 67-50
article.story: GREENSBORO, N.C. -- Ahmad Abdullah scored 17 points and North Carolina A&T beat Bethune-Cookman 67-50 on Monday night. The teams are now tied for eighth in the Mid-Eastern Athletic Conference with one game to play. Bruce Beckford added 13 points and eight rebounds and Arturs Bremers had 12 points, all on 3-pointers. The Aggies held a 34-26 rebounding advantage and blocked five shots. North Carolina A&T (9-21, 6-9) made a 12-3 run early in the first half, including a 3-pointer from Bremers, and led 30-24 at the break. The Aggies used a 15-6 run early in the second half, capped by a layup by Abdullah, to open a 12-point lead and Bethune-Cookman never got within seven points again. Bethune-Cookman (10-20, 6-9) was led by Ricky Johnson with 18 points, despite going 4 of 14 from the field, and Mikel Trapp had 14 points.
